---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { NOW_UPDATED } from "../consts";
---

<BaseLayout title="Now | Arun Setty" description="What I'm currently doing and thinking about.">
  <article class="now">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <header class="now-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">Now</span>
        <h1 class="now-title">What I'm doing now</h1>
        <p class="now-meta">Last updated: {NOW_UPDATED}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="now-rule"></div>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Day job</h2>
        <p>
          Co-founder and CTO at <a href="https://ur-ai.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ur AI</a>. Building AI products for structured workflows: document intelligence, automation, the long tail of operational work knowledge workers actually spend their day on. Owning product, engineering, and system architecture end-to-end. Most of my mental cycles go here.
        </p>

        <h2>Side projects</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Arise.</strong> A health-tech app that tracks daily vitals and visualizes progress through a gamified leveling system. In beta with about 20 people. Around 40% are active (using it at least once every two days), and the group has tracked over 5 million steps collectively. I'm currently studying power-user patterns to design nudges that get the rest of the group walking more.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Weekend hacker house.</strong> A small group of friends in Bangalore. Started after an Anthropic hackathon when we built something usable in a weekend and realized that being in the same room with a focused group was the unlock. Now it's a regular space: 5 to 6-hour Saturday sessions, pizza, laptops, a strong bias toward shipping. Arise came out of one of these.
        </p>

        <h2>Writing</h2>
        <p>
          One essay most days at <a href="/thoughts">Ephemeral Thoughts</a>. Latest is <a href="/thoughts/decisions-and-statistics">Decisions & Statistics</a>. Topics drift between behavior, decisions, systems thinking, and whatever I'm tinkering with that week.
        </p>

        <h2>Reading & watching</h2>
        <p>
          Whatever I'm in the middle of lives at <a href="/log">A·S·K Log</a>, with thoughts in the moment instead of polished retrospectives. Episode-level when something hits.
        </p>

        <h2>Thinking about</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The structured-workflow space, and what makes AI usable inside actual work rather than just chat</li>
          <li>Why pre-AI-era no-code patterns (constrained, spec-driven generation) might still beat raw LLM-only approaches for production software</li>
          <li>How weekend sessions with hard time constraints out-ship long deliberate planning cycles</li>
          <li>The relationship between an excellence reflex and pace, and whether they're actually in tension</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="now-note">
          This is a <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">/now page</a>, a snapshot of what I'm focused on at this point in my life. Updated when the focus shifts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .now {
    padding-top: 120px;
    padding-bottom: 80px;
  }

  .now-header {
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .now-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 12px 0 16px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .now-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .now-rule {
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--rule-color);
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  .now-note {
    margin-top: 56px !important;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-color);
    font-size: 0.92rem !important;
    color: var(--text-muted) !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
